                               p  o  l  y  m  e  c 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Software Requirements
---------------------
The polymec library requires the following software for installation:

  - A C compiler that adheres to (or aspires to) the C11 standard. 
    Currently, GCC 4.8 and Clang 3.4 are quite usable (though others
    may work as well).
  - CMake 2.8.5+ (found at http://www.cmake.org)
  - GNU Make

To build polymec on a UNIX-like system, use the following commands:

     $ make config
     $ make

Installation
------------
To install polymec, run

    $ make install

The default installation prefix is /usr/local. To pick an installation 
prefix for polymec pass prefix=[path] to make config. For example,

    $ make config prefix=~/myroot/

will cause polymec to be installed in ~/myroot/ when make install is run.

Other make commands
-------------------
   $ make uninstall 
          Removes all files installed by 'make install'.
   
   $ make clean 
          Removes all object files but retains the configuration options.
   
   $ make distclean 
          Performs clean and completely removes the build directory.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                  Instructions for particular machines
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

NERSC Edison (last updated 2/18/2015)
-------------------------------------

Make sure the following modules are loaded:
  cmake 
  silo
  PrgEnv-Intel

and then type

make config mpi=1 prefix=/prefix/for/polymec

adding any additional desired flags. Then:

make mpi=1 install

NERSC Hopper (last updated 5/8/2015)
------------------------------------

Load the following modules
  cmake
  silo
  PrgEnv-intel

and then type

make config mpi=1 prefix=/prefix/for/polymec 

followed by

make mpi=1 install
